The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Cricket clash
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Cricket clash
                            
	Mumbai, July 6 (PTI): Four persons were injured in a clash during a cricket match at the northeastern suburb of Deonar, police said today.        
	The groups belonging to two communities had gathered at a playground for the match and assaulted each other over a dispute, the police said, adding that they had to use tear gas to disperse the crowd. The injured have been admitted to a local hospital.        
	The situation is under control, the joint commissioner of police (law and order), who visited the spot, said.                                                                                                                                                                          
